com.frankly.franklysdk.authenticate

Class InsecureIdentityTokenGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.frankly.franklysdk.authenticate.BaseIdentityTokenGenerator
      • com.frankly.franklysdk.authenticate.InsecureIdentityTokenGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IdentityTokenGenerator

    public class InsecureIdentityTokenGenerator
extends BaseIdentityTokenGenerator
    Generates an insecure identity token.

    Insecurity

    Hard-coded secrets (authKey, authSecret, insecureKey) can cause severe security problems.
    And the use is limited to a debug environment.

    Warning!!! If you take risks, you can use this with adding the following configuration into AndroidManifest.xml.
      <meta-data
      android:name="com.frankly.franklysdk.allowInsecureAuth"
      android:value="true"/>
